<task id="030" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P23.A1 — Migrate IChatClient streaming tests batch 1 (Services/Ai/Chat/Streaming*)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-2-3, ichatclient, p23-a, bff-api, testing, streaming</tags>
    <parallel-group>23-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Named test files under Services/Ai/Chat/Streaming* are disjoint from sibling batch 031 (Services/Ai/Capabilities/Streaming*); no shared file targets</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Migrate the ~15 IChatClient streaming tests under `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/Streaming*`
    from broken NSubstitute auto-mock setups to the `AsyncEnumerableHelpers` infrastructure shipped
    by Phase 1 task 015 (FR-06). Per design.md §3.4 (failure clustering), the IChatClient streaming
    cluster is the largest single failure cluster — NSubstitute does not auto-mock `IAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;`
    returns, so streaming-completion tests fail at the first `await foreach`.

    For each test:
    1. Identify the broken IChatClient setup (NSubstitute `Returns(...)` against a streaming method)
    2. Replace with `AsyncEnumerableHelpers.FromValues(...)` (or the Microsoft-shipped equivalent
       per Phase 0 D-01 verdict) producing the same response sequence
    3. Apply `[Trait("status", "repaired")]` per project CLAUDE.md §6.2 taxonomy
    4. Run the affected test class; verify Pass

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-02 + design.md §4.1: this is repair, NOT rewrite. If ANY file's diff
    would exceed 50% line replacement, HALT and file
    `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/escalations/rewrite-request-T-030-{FileName}.md`
    per §4.8 escalation procedure. Do NOT proceed without owner approval.

    NO production code changes (NFR-01). Per project CLAUDE.md §6.2, every touched test ends in
    `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`, `real-bug-pending-fix`, `flaky-quarantined`, OR is archived
    via rename to `*.cs.archived-2026-MM-DD`. `Failed` is FORBIDDEN at project close.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET test repair specialist; expert in IAsyncEnumerable mock patterns and Microsoft.Extensions.AI.</role>

  <goal>
    ~15 streaming-related test files under `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/Streaming*`
    are migrated to use `AsyncEnumerableHelpers`. All migrated tests Pass. Every touched test has
    `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`. Cluster verification (task 032) will gate the IChatClient
    cluster overall.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="decision">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/decisions/D-01-async-enumerable-helper.md</file>
    <file purpose="helper">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Mocks/AsyncEnumerableHelpers.cs</file>
    <file purpose="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">MUST NOT modify production code in `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">MUST NOT replace &gt;50% of any file without §4.8 escalation BEFORE work proceeds</constraint>
    <constraint source="§6.2">Every touched test gets `[Trait("status", "repaired")]` (or `real-bug-pending-fix` / `flaky-quarantined` / archive)</constraint>
    <constraint source="§4.5">MUST NOT touch `CustomWebAppFactory.cs`</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-03">MUST NOT increase BFF DI registration count via test scaffolding</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-14">All IChatClient streaming tests must end in §6.2 final end-state</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §3.4 (failure clustering), the IChatClient streaming / IAsyncEnumerable mocking
      cluster is ~30-50 tests — the largest single failure cluster in the suite. Root cause:
      NSubstitute auto-mock returns null/default for IAsyncEnumerable returns instead of an empty
      sequence, so any `await foreach` in production code throws or hangs. Phase 1 task 015 (P1.B)
      shipped `AsyncEnumerableHelpers` (or equivalent Microsoft package per D-01). This task
      consumes that helper to repair batch 1 (Services/Ai/Chat/Streaming*); batch 2 (task 031)
      handles Services/Ai/Capabilities/Streaming*; task 032 verifies the cluster.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="015" status="not-started">AsyncEnumerableHelpers shipped + has its own tests</dependency>
      <dependency task="014" status="not-started">Compile health verified after P1.A batches</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/Streaming*.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/*StreamingTests.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Mocks/AsyncEnumerableHelpers.cs</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read D-01 decision file to confirm whether to use hand-rolled `AsyncEnumerableHelpers` or Microsoft-shipped equivalent.</step>
    <step order="2">From Phase 0 baseline TRX (`baseline/test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx`), identify failing tests under `Services/Ai/Chat/Streaming*`. Expected ~15 tests across multiple files (first batch of the ~30-50 cluster).</step>
    <step order="3">For each affected test file: read current source; identify the NSubstitute setup of IChatClient streaming method (typically `GetStreamingResponseAsync` or `CompleteStreamingAsync`).</step>
    <step order="4">Compute pre-edit line count per file. If any planned edit exceeds 50% of file lines → HALT, file `escalations/rewrite-request-T-030-{FileName}.md`, await owner approval before proceeding on that file.</step>
    <step order="5">Replace the broken setup with `AsyncEnumerableHelpers.FromValues(...)` constructing the expected streaming response. Preserve assertions.</step>
    <step order="6">Apply `[Trait("status", "repaired")]` at class level (or per-method if class is mixed-status).</step>
    <step order="7">After each file: run `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~&lt;ClassName&gt;"` and verify Pass.</step>
    <step order="8">Final batch verification: `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Services.Ai.Chat.Streaming"` shows zero failures for this batch's named files.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md` with file list + per-file LOC delta + tests-now-passing count.</step>
    <step order="10">Verify `git status` shows NO modifications under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test (per-file iterative + batch verification)</tool>
    <tool name="git">status (verify NFR-01)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/Streaming*.cs (repaired, ~15 files)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md (updated with batch outcome)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All ~15 batch-1 streaming tests Pass under `dotnet test --filter`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-file diff is &lt;50% line replacement (NFR-02); if exceeded, escalation file exists in `escalations/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every touched test has `[Trait("status", "repaired")]` (or another §6.2 final end-state)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`git status` shows zero changes under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`CustomWebAppFactory.cs` is NOT modified</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new DI registrations added (NFR-03 preserved)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
